13 July 2010Following President Jacob Zuma and FIFA President Sepp Blatter s assessment of the 2010 FIFA World Cup, Government will hold a detailed briefing on its performance and legacy related to the World Cup.The briefing will take place as follows:Date: Wednesday, 14 July 2010 Time: 11:00 Venue: Room 153, Union BuildingsNB: There will be a video link-up to Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street, Cape Town.For media enquiries contact: Pheliswa Sebati Cell: 082 413 4609OrLiezil Cerf Cell: 076 778 2380Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)